
---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About - Tech & Trails"
  description="Learn about the developer behind Tech & Trails blog."
>
  <nav class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4">
        <a href="/" class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-gray-900 hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">
          Work From Loam
        </a>
        <div class="flex space-x-6">
          <a href="/" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors font-medium">Posts</a>
          <a href="/about" class="text-gray-900 font-medium">About</a>
          <a href="https://youtube.com/@workfromloam" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors font-medium flex items-center gap-1">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M23.498 6.186a3.016 3.016 0 0 0-2.122-2.136C19.505 3.545 12 3.545 12 3.545s-7.505 0-9.377.505A3.017 3.017 0 0 0 .502 6.186C0 8.07 0 12 0 12s0 3.93.502 5.814a3.016 3.016 0 0 0 2.122 2.136c1871.505 9.376.505 9.376.505s7.505 0 9.377-.505a3.015 3.015 0 0 0 2.122-2.136C24 15.93 24 12 24 12s0-3.93-.502-5.814zM9.545 15.568V8.432L15.818 12l-6.273 3.568z"/>
            </svg>
            YouTube
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">About Tech & Trails</h1>
      
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Welcome to Tech & Trails, where code meets mountain adventures. I'm a game developer, parent, and passionate mountain biker trying to balance it all in the beautiful chaos of modern adult life.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          After spending my days building virtual worlds in the video game industry, I find peace and perspective on real mountain trails. This blog explores that intersection – how the problem-solving skills from development translate to technical terrain, how early morning rides fuel creativity for afternoon coding sessions, and how to maintain passions while juggling family responsibilities.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4 mt-8">What You'll Find Here</h2>
        
        <ul class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Mountain Biking Adventures:</strong> Trail reports, gear reviews, and stories from the mountains</li>
          <li><strong>Game Development Insights:</strong> Technical posts about building games, from TypeScript tips to engine architecture</li>
          <li><strong>Work-Life Balance:</strong> Real talk about being a parent, professional, and passionate rider</li>
          <li><strong>Community Building:</strong> How mountain biking and tech overlap in unexpected ways</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4 mt-8">Connect</h2>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Have questions, trail recommendations, or want to discuss the latest in game development? 
          Drop a comment on any post – I use GitHub-based commenting, so you'll need a GitHub account to participate. 
          It's a great way to keep the conversation focused on the intersection of tech and outdoor adventures.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
